    <h1>How to Learn HTML</h1>
    <h2>Start with the Basics</h2>
    <p class="paragraph-style">Begin by understanding the fundamental structure of an HTML document, including the &lt;!DOCTYPE&gt;, &lt;html&gt;, &lt;head&gt;, and &lt;body&gt; tags. Learn about essential HTML elements like headings (&lt;h1&gt; to &lt;h6&gt;), paragraphs (&lt;p&gt;), and line breaks (&lt;br&gt;).</p>

    <h2>Explore HTML Elements and Attributes</h2>
    <p>Familiarize yourself with various HTML elements and their purposes, such as &lt;div&gt;, &lt;span&gt;, &lt;ul&gt;, &lt;ol&gt;, &lt;li&gt;, &lt;table&gt;, &lt;img&gt;, and &lt;a&gt;. Understand how to use attributes like `class`, `id`, `src`, `alt`, and `href` to add functionality and styling to these elements.</p>

    <h2 class="important-text">Learn About Text Formatting</h2>
    <p>Discover how to format text using elements like &lt;b&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;, &lt;i&gt;, &lt;em&gt;, &lt;u&gt;, and &lt;mark&gt; to emphasize and structure your content.</p>

    <h2>Understand HTML Links and Images</h2>
    <p>Master the creation of hyperlinks using the &lt;a&gt; tag to connect different web pages and resources. Learn how to embed images using the &lt;img&gt; tag and understand the importance of the `src` and `alt` attributes.</p>

    <img id="main-image" src="placeholder.jpg" alt="An example of HTML structure" width="300">
    <p>Remember to replace "placeholder.jpg" with an actual image file.</p>

    <h2>Structure Content with Lists and Tables</h2>
    <p>Learn how to organize information using unordered (&lt;ul&gt;) and ordered (&lt;ol&gt;) lists. Understand how to create and structure tabular data using the &lt;table&gt;, &lt;tr&gt;, &lt;th&gt;, and &lt;td&gt; elements.</p>

    <ul class="unordered-list">
        <li>Start with online tutorials and documentation.</li>
        <li>Practice writing HTML code regularly.</li>
        <li>Build small projects to apply your knowledge.</li>
    </ul>

    <ol class="ordered-list">
        <li>Set up a basic HTML file.</li>
        <li>Add headings and paragraphs.</li>
        <li>Include links and images.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2 id="section2">Styling Your HTML with CSS</h2>
    <p class="paragraph-style special-font">While this page focuses on HTML, it's crucial to understand that CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) is used to style the appearance of your HTML elements. You can apply CSS using inline styles, internal stylesheets (within &lt;style&gt; tags), or, preferably, external stylesheets linked in the &lt;head&gt; section.</p>

    <div class="padded-element margin-element">Continue your learning journey by exploring CSS properties for text, fonts, lists, borders, padding, and margins!</div>

